  Grand Prince: Drawing Love

2
00:00:32,860 --> 00:00:41,860

3
00:00:44,140 --> 00:00:49,930
  Grand Prince: Drawing Love

4
00:00:51,750 --> 00:00:56,860
  Recap of past episodes

5
00:00:56,860 --> 00:00:57,970
  Your Majesty!

6
00:00:57,970 --> 00:00:58,810
  Your Majesty!

7
00:00:58,810 --> 00:01:00,860
  The king is unconscious?

8
00:01:00,860 --> 00:01:04,680
  The barbarians are attacking from the north, and the king is unconscious.

9
00:01:04,680 --> 00:01:08,970
  We desperately need a strong leader who can face this crisis head on.

10
00:01:08,970 --> 00:01:11,840
  As they wish, let us select a saejae (King's younger brother as an heir).

11
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:14,660
  Be a saejae? Why would I?

12
00:01:14,660 --> 00:01:17,670
  It cannot be your brother. You have to accept it.

13
00:01:17,670 --> 00:01:19,930
  As his brother, I can't approve of this marriage.

14
00:01:19,930 --> 00:01:21,830
  I have already completed my introduction to the queen dowager.

15
00:01:21,830 --> 00:01:25,040
  The woman I love is to become my sister-in-law. Is that even possible?

16
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:28,850
  Grand Prince Eun Seong and I are connected by fate. No matter how much you hate it,

17
00:01:28,850 --> 00:01:30,800
  you can't end our connection.

18
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,340
  You will be able to see the power of a person who overcomes heaven's will.

19
00:01:34,340 --> 00:01:36,140
  The saejae His Majesty and I have decided on

20
00:01:36,140 --> 00:01:38,880
  is not Grand Prince Jin Yang, but Grand Prince Eun Seong.

21
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:40,290
  Did you know this?

22
00:01:40,290 --> 00:01:43,600
  Mother has been thinking of Eun Seong as saejae all along, not me.

23
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:46,570
  I'm going to take Eun Seong to the battlefield.

24
00:01:46,570 --> 00:01:50,800
  If he is an existence that endangers my nephew's future, I must get rid of him.

25
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:53,470
  I guess you were nothing to him.

26
00:01:53,470 --> 00:01:57,660
  That you're his fated lover,  isn't it the most terrible fate of all?

27
00:01:58,770 --> 00:02:00,340
  Is there something wrong?

28
00:02:00,340 --> 00:02:03,130
  You've deceived me again, Your Highness.

29
00:02:03,130 --> 00:02:05,150
  I hear you're going to the battlefield.

30
00:02:05,150 --> 00:02:06,170
  It's not like that.

31
00:02:06,170 --> 00:02:07,830
  Then, are you not going?

32
00:02:07,830 --> 00:02:12,410
  I have come to fully understand how insignificant I am to you, Grand Prince.

33
00:02:17,430 --> 00:02:19,310
  Lady!

34
00:02:19,970 --> 00:02:22,370

Signs affixed to the gate as a talisman (bujeok) for protection from disaster,  to bless the house, and to ward off evil spirits.

35
00:02:22,370 --> 00:02:25,180
  Am I really nothing to you?

36
00:02:25,180 --> 00:02:28,120
  Will you not go if I tell you not to?

37
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:30,250
  I will make sure to come back alive.

38
00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:32,890
  My life is yours.

39
00:02:32,890 --> 00:02:36,230
  It's a pledge of loyalty that I offer to you.

40
00:02:36,230 --> 00:02:39,020
 I wish to be of help to you in your great cause.

41
00:02:39,020 --> 00:02:44,780
  I will stake my life and the fate of my family for the sake of your cause.

42
00:02:45,790 --> 00:02:48,150
  Is this the place you wanted to visit with me?

43
00:02:48,150 --> 00:02:52,300
  There's something I need to do with Your Highness here.

44
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:57,790
  I, Seong Ja Hyeon, take my fated love, Lee Hwi, as my husband.

45
00:02:57,800 --> 00:03:02,560
  I swear to love and treasure her with all my heart.

46
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:06,800
  I swear. Don't forget

47
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:09,870
  that I'll be waiting for you.

48
00:03:12,010 --> 00:03:14,520
  Episode 7

49
00:04:00,050 --> 00:04:01,520
From which household are you?

50
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:06,680
I am from the household of Grand Prince Yang Ahn.

51
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:08,890
I am from Chief Scholar's household.

52
00:04:09,810 --> 00:04:12,250
But, there must be a lot of people in your household.

53
00:04:12,250 --> 00:04:16,680
Why would they send a young one to such a harsh place?

54
00:04:26,580 --> 00:04:30,220
Ja Hyeon? To see your brother off...

55
00:04:31,230 --> 00:04:33,640
Where did this girl go again?

56
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:36,370
Did she go by herself to see him off?

57
00:04:46,610 --> 00:04:49,130
What is this?

58
00:04:52,980 --> 00:04:57,360
 Mother, I will see Brother and the grand prince off and return.

59
00:04:57,360 --> 00:05:00,720
 Even if I'm late, don't worry too much.

60
00:05:01,410 --> 00:05:04,360
If she were going to see her brother off, she should've gone with us.

61
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:08,010
What secret plan did she have to leave the house alone?

62
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:12,830
Oh, my!

63
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:17,420
- Aigoo!  
 - Madam!

64
00:05:17,420 --> 00:05:20,580
- Hey, hey, that's a rag! 
 - Oh, a rag!

65
00:05:20,580 --> 00:05:22,410
Ah, what should I do?

66
00:05:22,410 --> 00:05:24,460
Aigoo, aigoo, aigoo, I don't need any of this.

67
00:05:24,460 --> 00:05:26,950
Go and get Ja Hyeon. When did she leave?

68
00:05:26,950 --> 00:05:29,470
You knew already, didn't you?

69
00:05:29,470 --> 00:05:30,810
She isn't home?

70
00:05:30,810 --> 00:05:32,950
She went to see Grand Prince Eun Seong off.

71
00:05:32,950 --> 00:05:34,590
Alone?!

72
00:05:34,590 --> 00:05:38,220
That's why it is strange.

73
00:05:38,220 --> 00:05:40,560
She didn't pack her stuff and go after him, did she?

74
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:43,530
Check if there is anything missing!

75
00:05:43,530 --> 00:05:45,800
Madam, I didn't know.

76
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:48,390
I didn't help with anything whatsoever this time!

77
00:05:48,390 --> 00:05:50,210
I'm saying that I didn't know that the lady had left!

78
00:05:50,210 --> 00:05:52,480
If you knew but didn't tell, you'd deserve to die.

79
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:54,470
Even if you didn't know at all, you deserve to be kicked out!

80
00:05:54,470 --> 00:05:58,230
How can you be a personal maid and have no clue at all?

81
00:05:58,230 --> 00:06:01,660
You know how challenging the lady can be.

82
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:06,330
If she went to the battlefield, how can we bring her back?

83
00:06:06,330 --> 00:06:09,180
I suppose we have to tell His Excellency, right?

84
00:06:09,180 --> 00:06:12,070
What should we do with this? Ah, what do we do?

85
00:06:12,070 --> 00:06:14,670
Oh, what do I do with this?

86
00:06:28,580 --> 00:06:30,290
Are you leaving the palace?

87
00:06:30,290 --> 00:06:33,850
You have not left yet?  I thought you were leaving after seeing them off.

88
00:06:33,850 --> 00:06:37,760
People with purpose have all gone on their way.

89
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:40,160
I've been hesitating out of embarrassment over being left behind.

90
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:45,050
Protecting the capital city is as important. Please do not be too hard on yourself.

91
00:06:45,050 --> 00:06:49,920
Seeing your son off to the battlefield has to have upset you greatly I'm sure.

92
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:54,040
I wonder if we can commiserate over tea at your house.

93
00:06:54,570 --> 00:06:56,940
Will you allow me, please?

94
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:26,870
What are you doing?

95
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:28,520
It's nothing.

96
00:07:28,520 --> 00:07:31,270
Why don't you come here and share the fire?

97
00:07:40,770 --> 00:07:44,630
The fastest way is to cut through inland, this way.

98
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:47,540
If we take the road by the sea, it will take a few more days.

99
00:07:47,540 --> 00:07:51,990
Going through the mountains in this cold weather will cause hardship to our troops.

100
00:07:51,990 --> 00:07:55,270
Let's take this road so that we can rest

101
00:07:55,270 --> 00:07:57,250
at a government house rather than in the village.

102
00:07:58,390 --> 00:08:01,770
Wouldn't our citizens in the north continue to suffer during that time?

103
00:08:01,770 --> 00:08:03,760
Even though it's difficult if we travel as quickly as possible—

104
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:07,920
If we travel more than 30 li (15 km) in a day, soldiers will inevitably fall behind.

105
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:12,820
We cannot win the battle against vicious Jurchens if our soldiers become exhausted.

106
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:16,000
Let's go this way.

107
00:08:19,080 --> 00:08:21,270
Food will be served now.

108
00:08:43,570 --> 00:08:46,930
Do we usually eat this well on a battlefield?

109
00:08:58,920 --> 00:09:01,060
You should eat a little more.

110
00:09:01,060 --> 00:09:04,180
I wonder what the state of the soldiers' food is.

111
00:09:05,180 --> 00:09:07,060
I'm going to walk around a bit.

112
00:09:07,060 --> 00:09:11,590
Temperatures will drop when the sun goes down.  How will they manage the night?

113
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,700
I will guide you.

114
00:09:33,830 --> 00:09:35,740
Here you go.

115
00:09:40,710 --> 00:09:43,160
But now, how come your water isn't frozen?

116
00:09:43,160 --> 00:09:47,520
I put some salt in mine. Saltwater doesn't freeze, right?

117
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:50,450
Ah, this guy is quite smart.

118
00:09:50,450 --> 00:09:53,880
Hurry and eat. Even though it's frozen rice,

119
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:56,960
- you have to force yourself to eat it. 
- Yes.

120
00:10:04,820 --> 00:10:06,290
Damn it.

121
00:10:24,690 --> 00:10:27,150
Do we have injured soldiers already?

122
00:10:27,150 --> 00:10:30,460
Some have injured their backs from carrying the cargo,

123
00:10:30,460 --> 00:10:33,900
others have caught a cold.

124
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:36,180
Are we having them sleep outside too?

125
00:10:36,180 --> 00:10:38,780
We don't have enough tent quarters to house regular soldiers.

126
00:10:38,780 --> 00:10:44,630
Even the sons from noble families have to sleep outside due to the shortage of tent quarters.

127
00:10:52,570 --> 00:10:56,250
Please have the sick and injured soldiers use my tent quarters.

128
00:10:57,330 --> 00:10:59,240
Your Highness, to go as far as that...

129
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:02,610
Our progress could be delayed due to their illness and injury.

130
00:11:02,610 --> 00:11:05,430
Please do as I ask.  It's an order.

131
00:11:09,570 --> 00:11:13,480
Go find ones with most severe illness or injuries and move them to the grand prince's tent.

132
00:11:13,540 --> 00:11:15,550
Yes, yes, yes.

133
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:20,170
Thank you.

134
00:11:20,170 --> 00:11:22,060
Everyone be seated.

135
00:11:26,880 --> 00:11:31,030
Why can't he look after me half as much as he looks after the soldiers?

136
00:11:31,030 --> 00:11:35,230
Am I a stranger?  I'll be his brother soon.

137
00:11:36,230 --> 00:11:40,050
What're you doing?  All of you injured and wounded, come forward.

138
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:45,310
Go.  Go on in!

139
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:08,750
Ma'am!

140
00:12:08,750 --> 00:12:10,610
Ma'am, ma'am!

141
00:12:10,610 --> 00:12:13,540
His Excellency has come home from the palace.

142
00:12:30,770 --> 00:12:34,430
This is the best tea I've had recently.

143
00:12:34,430 --> 00:12:37,180
Did you not have something to say?

144
00:12:37,180 --> 00:12:39,690
I understand my brother proposed to your daughter.

145
00:12:39,690 --> 00:12:43,820
My wife and daughter have greeted Queen Dowager.

146
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:48,450
I did not know you had the ambition to become the gukgu (king's father-in-law).

147
00:12:50,980 --> 00:12:56,680
While it is an honor to become family with the king, it is not something my family wished.

148
00:12:56,680 --> 00:13:01,930
The fact that Queen Mother wants to install that child (Eun Seong) as saejae

149
00:13:01,930 --> 00:13:05,080
doesn't mean she wants to give him the throne.

150
00:13:06,730 --> 00:13:09,620
We have to wait for the wonja (king's baby son) to grow up,

151
00:13:09,620 --> 00:13:15,730
but we've had to adopt a temporary measure due to the situation in the north.  This I know.

152
00:13:15,730 --> 00:13:19,140
If Grand Prince Eun Seong is installed as the saejae later on,

153
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:23,310
do you think your future will be secure?

154
00:13:25,890 --> 00:13:30,190
Emperor Jianwen of Ming Dynasty slaughtered his uncles as soon as he ascended to the throne.

155
00:13:30,190 --> 00:13:35,960
It's normal to get rid of dangerous obstacles first when one takes power.

156
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:44,350
Do not place your one and only precious daughter on the path of perilous future.

157
00:13:44,350 --> 00:13:49,210
If you are behind my brother, Eun Seong's power will grow.

158
00:13:49,210 --> 00:13:54,300
When he becomes an adult, Wonja will be resentful of such an uncle.

159
00:13:55,950 --> 00:13:58,760
Is this a threat?

160
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:00,990
Of course not.

161
00:14:00,990 --> 00:14:03,880
I'm trying to share the will of the previous king with you.

162
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:07,690
My wise father gave me an agreeable path.

163
00:14:07,690 --> 00:14:10,110
Why do you think he did?

164
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:17,210
Don't look at it as though it's someone else's business.

165
00:14:17,210 --> 00:14:22,120
You know how cold Queen Dowager can be at times.

166
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:24,390
You know that very well already.

167
00:14:24,390 --> 00:14:26,990
Excellency!

168
00:14:26,990 --> 00:14:29,990
We need to go and get our Ja Hyeon.

169
00:14:29,990 --> 00:14:32,690
Without an ounce of fear, she followed the military...

170
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:38,080
What does that mean? What did our Ja Hyeon do?

171
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:41,370
What I mean is, she's gone to see his brother off.

172
00:14:41,370 --> 00:14:42,930
What?  Where does she think that is?

173
00:14:42,930 --> 00:14:45,140
I will bring her back.

174
00:14:59,920 --> 00:15:04,180
I was already putting a team together to deliver supplies there.

175
00:15:04,180 --> 00:15:06,370
Since I will be there, I'll bring your daughter back.

176
00:15:06,370 --> 00:15:09,260
We will look after it ourselves.  Please do not concern—

177
00:15:09,260 --> 00:15:12,400
Your child's innocent action can cause a misunderstanding, right?

178
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:17,270
If Grand Prince would help, our hearts will be relieved.

179
00:15:42,380 --> 00:15:44,270
It's all done.

180
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:50,180
What's your identity?

181
00:15:50,960 --> 00:15:54,280
Without permission, you left the camp during dinner. Are you a spy from the Jurchens or

182
00:15:54,280 --> 00:15:59,420
an escapee who betrayed his comrades?

183
00:16:00,020 --> 00:16:02,110
Speak, I say!

184
00:16:09,370 --> 00:16:10,940
My lady!

185
00:16:15,870 --> 00:16:18,040
How are you here?

186
00:16:21,350 --> 00:16:23,070
What's with this look of you?

187
00:16:23,070 --> 00:16:24,680
No, I just...

188
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:26,830
When did you come here?

189
00:16:26,830 --> 00:16:28,870
Is your body okay?

190
00:16:28,870 --> 00:16:31,950
Why did you follow me here, being a woman of the inner house (wife)?

191
00:16:31,950 --> 00:16:33,820
Are you hungry?

192
00:16:33,820 --> 00:16:37,150
What were you thinking that you did this?

193
00:16:37,150 --> 00:16:39,990
You said the north was colder.

194
00:16:41,630 --> 00:16:42,940
Just for this?

195
00:16:42,940 --> 00:16:46,730
You came all the way here for this?  Are you in your right mind?

196
00:16:46,730 --> 00:16:50,740
One more time. One more time, I wanted to see you.

197
00:16:52,010 --> 00:16:55,660
I wanted to have you wear the clothes I made myself

198
00:16:55,660 --> 00:16:58,830
so that you could be a little warmer on the cold, long path.

199
00:17:00,930 --> 00:17:05,080
I wanted to finish it last night so that I could give it to you before you left but

200
00:17:05,080 --> 00:17:08,400
I was not quite finished so...

201
00:17:29,660 --> 00:17:32,560
What am I to do with you, lady?

202
00:17:44,970 --> 00:17:47,580
Since I delivered this, it's okay.

203
00:17:47,580 --> 00:17:49,300
Now, I will leave.

204
00:17:49,300 --> 00:17:53,350
Don't you know the days are shorter in the winter? The sun will set soon.

205
00:17:55,190 --> 00:17:56,650
I can just walk all night.

206
00:17:56,650 --> 00:18:00,610
Do you think I could just send you off like that?

207
00:18:00,610 --> 00:18:05,810
Stay at my tent tonight.  I will send you off with an escort first thing in the morning.

208
00:18:05,810 --> 00:18:08,710
If I'd have known, I would have kept the tent empty.

209
00:18:08,710 --> 00:18:12,600
I'm dressed as a man.  I can sleep outside.

210
00:18:21,690 --> 00:18:24,430
Must you go tonight?

211
00:18:24,430 --> 00:18:27,360
You don't have to go yourself.

212
00:18:27,360 --> 00:18:30,790
My uncle has put his life on the line for me

213
00:18:30,790 --> 00:18:33,280
and has taken my brother to the frontline instead of me.

214
00:18:33,280 --> 00:18:36,300
If I don't support them as much as I can from here, what will I be?

215
00:18:36,300 --> 00:18:38,590
Enter the palace tomorrow.

216
00:18:38,590 --> 00:18:41,370
We have to find out about the king's condition.

217
00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:43,540
Yes, Your Excellency.

218
00:18:43,540 --> 00:18:48,980
Please console my mother's weary heart and look around  (spy on)  the queen's quarters.

219
00:19:52,260 --> 00:19:54,260
I can just sleep outside.

220
00:19:54,260 --> 00:19:56,330
You could freeze to death.

